LAUSANNE - J r me Valcke, former secretary general of FIFA, has filed an appeal at the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS) against the decision issued by the FIFA Appeal Committee last June in which he was banned from taking part in any football-related activity for 10 years.READ: FIFA fires deputy secretary general, Markus KattnerFormer FIFA secretary general Jerome Valcke appeals to Court of Arbitration for Sport against 10-year ban from footballThe parties will first exchange written submissions and a panel of three arbitrators will be constituted.The panel will then issue directions with respect to the holding of a hearing. Following the hearing, the panel will deliberate and at a later date, will issue a decision.African News Agency